{{- define "wake_blocked_tasks" -}}
Tasks are BLOCKED. Analyze and resolve immediately:

1. Read blocked tasks from blackboard — understand blocker_reason
2. Determine if blocker is:
   - Missing dependency → create prerequisite task (execute {{.ToolPrefix}}liza_add_tasks tool NOW)
   - Spec ambiguity → clarify spec, then supersede with corrected task
   - External dependency → document, possibly supersede task
   - Wrong approach → supersede task, create alternative (execute tools NOW)
3. For each blocked task, decide action:
   - To supersede (create clean replacement):
   Example supersede workflow:
   a. Re-read the task via {{.ToolPrefix}}liza_get tasks/<task-id> to confirm it is still BLOCKED.
      If status changed (e.g., task was claimed), skip — the task is being actively worked.
   b. Execute tool: {{.ToolPrefix}}liza_add_tasks with {"tasks": [{"id": "task-4", ...}], "agent_id": "{{.AgentID}}"} (create replacement tasks)
   c. Execute tool: {{.ToolPrefix}}liza_supersede_task with {"task_id": "task-3", "replacement_ids": ["task-4", "task-5"], "reason": "Split due to complexity", "agent_id": "{{.AgentID}}"}
   d. Execute tool: {{.ToolPrefix}}liza_wt_delete with {"task_id": "task-3", "agent_id": "{{.AgentID}}"} (if worktree exists)
4. After analyzing each blocked task:
   - If you resolved it (superseded): no further action needed for that task
   - If you CANNOT resolve it (genuine spec ambiguity, external dependency): call {{.ToolPrefix}}liza_assess_blocked to record your assessment
     Execute tool: {{.ToolPrefix}}liza_assess_blocked with {"task_id": "<task-id>", "note": "<why it cannot be resolved now>"}
     This prevents re-waking for the same unresolvable block. The task will trigger again only when new information arrives (dependency changes, human notes).
5. Execute all state-modifying tools in this session. Do NOT defer.

Do NOT call {{.ToolPrefix}}liza_sprint_checkpoint. If you cannot resolve a blocker, assess it and exit. Other tasks must continue uninterrupted.
{{- end -}}
